<br>
Also hope updated means that at least the ethereal parchments will drop off more mobs. And maybe a bit more commonly too. While it's been a bit frustrating to find them, I am glad VI chose to start off with more limited drop rates and leave room to adjust upwards. Alot of folks consider the lowering of drop rates in Luclin to have been a nerf, really to me I thought it was really odd to see nearly every mob dropping a spell, and some dropping two or three. Of course people were angry when the drop rates were reduced. But leaving yourself room to improve drop rates will usually make folks happy since it will not feel like a nerf. Hoping some of the loot drops are the same as the rewards for some of the tougher encounters have been kinda depressing (though some are excellant IMO). Same deal, just no more epic ratio weapons dropping off yard trash, if they need to be improved they can be and folks will be happpy. Better than putting in something that is unbalanced and later fixing it and everyone being unhappy because of the &quot;nerf&quot;. If that's in fact what they are doing, then kudo's.<br>
<br>
Ideallly it'd be nice if an xp group could average a spell per person in a typical playing session. In a week of playing, I've gotten one spell, at this rate, I might have all my spells for 61 in three months if I get no duplicates or level 62 spells. That's just way too rare IMO. Course I can trade duplicates, but only if it's a spell someone would want (let's face it, most mages will probably get stuck selling the focus necklace summon to a vendor since I don't think many will actually want it).<br>
