<br>
I so have to agree, there has been none of what the more cynical players call the classic SOE &quot;bait and switch&quot; in this expansion. Before this patch many players were fearful of an exp nerf for places like Plane of Valor, but there's nothing in the message about it (which doesn't mean it didn't happen!).<br>
<br>
Loot drops feel about right, and exp is decent if you venture to the planes and very good if you pass the difficult Trials and other encounters. I sincerely hope that this is part of a plan for this expansion which is proof that they are sticking to their &quot;levelling is something that will happen naturally rather than be a chore&quot; promises, and not a glaring oversight their doctors are desperately trying to come up with a good spin for so they can nerf it.<br>
<br>
I just wish I was sure of this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Luclin bruised me in many ways, especially after CoH's continual and gradual nerfing. I'm more critical of content, and treat the good stuff like a treasured morsel I must wring every fleeting moment of joy from. The fear of stuff being nerfed is everywhere, in particular on the &quot;big&quot; forums - how many posts have you seen about people finding great drops / parchments / exp and being unwilling to post about it?<br>
<br>
Sure, part of that is greed or a fear of their discovery being swamped with hunters, but at least a part of it is the ever-present threat of the Bat. For the good of the game they have to put the bat back into the cupboard for a while, even if there is mildly overpowering content. Exploits and game-breaking bugs need to be fixed, but random assaults form the bat need to stop, at least fro a time IMHO <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kinelaria>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 436<br> <font color=#333333>(10/31/02 12:07:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7668.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Patch Message October 31 2002</span><hr size=1> I think the only disappointments I've had this expansion:<br>
- Spells too hard to get (doesn't help Inny players hate mages, so getting into good groups is a real chore)<br>
- Plane of Disease is just very boring to me (green goo, green goo, oh look a spider came over from PoN, green goo, BROWN  GOO WOW!, green goo, green goo, hey look a plague rat ported up from Ak'kanon, green goo, green goo... you get the picture)<br>
- The small group encounters didn't work as I thought they'd been advertised, i.e. seperate groups being able to run the same event. While they can do this, they cannot do it simultaneously. Leads to lines to these events that can get quite long and the problems with lines of course, line breakers who jump past groups who've been waiting their turn.<br>
<br>
But the pro's I just don't think I could list here entirely. The great bulk of this expansion has been really cool. I'm sure they will iron out the issues we have. Maybe not entirely how we'd like them to, but I'm sure we'll at least be content with what they do.<br>
<br>
Just realized Servant of Ro and Host of the Elements were not mentioned in the patch. I really hate losing control of my normal pet while using the servant. Don't mind neccessarily that the servant is uncontrollable so long as it stays only on the mob I had targetted when I summoned it. Though would be best if pet commands were sent and accepted by all pets you have active. Also hoping at some point they raise it's level so it actually can land spells on higher level mobs (Servant of Ro that is, Host looks like it does fair damage against stuff).<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
Taeru<br>
Lana<br>
